    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "9694",
      "1935\nTHE FIRST PLANE TO INAUGURATE COMMERCIAL PASSENGER SERVICE ACROSS THE\nPACIFIC FROM SAN FRANCISCO TO MANILA AND THEN ON TO HONG KONG. THE\nFIRST FLIGHT TO MANILA TOOK 59-HOURS, 47-MINUTES. THE FAMOUS M-130\nHAD A WINGSPREAD OF 130-FEET AND A LENGTH OF 90-FEET. THE CLIPPER\nCARRIED UP TO 46-48 PASSENGERS AT A HIGH SPEED OF 180-MILES-PER-HOUR;\nA POWER PLANT OF FOUR PRATT \u0026 WHITNEY R-1830 TYPE 830 HORSEPOWER WITH A\nRANGE OF 3,200-MILES. THE MOST. FAMOUS M-130 WAS THE \"CHINA CLIPPER,\""
    ],
